      "content": "it still feels like you're being a bit evasive. you said the duty to protect people is a \"near-absolute moral obligation,\" but then you compare it to \"national stability.\" isn't it kind of a stretch to weigh the survival of a person against the abstract idea of a border? it feels like the security argument is just a way to justify ignoring human rights.",
